dat<-read.csv("trace_master.csv",header=TRUE)
dat[which(dat$Action=="Opened" | dat$Action=="Closed"),3]<-paste(dat[which(dat$Action=="Opened" | dat$Action=="Closed"),3],dat[which(dat$Action=="Opened" | dat$Action=="Closed"),8],sep="")

###Merge wizard and helper
#wizards
teacher.indecies<-grepl("w",dat$studentid,ignore.case = TRUE)
dat$studentid[teacher.indecies]<-"Wizard"
#remove helpers
teacher.indecies<-grepl("h",dat$studentid,ignore.case = TRUE)
dat$studentid[teacher.indecies]<-"Wizard"







###Subset data
chat.indecies<-dat$Action=="SentChatMessage" | dat$ContextValue3=="BB1" | dat$ContextValue3=="BB2" | dat$ContextValue3=="BB3"| dat$ContextValue3=="BB4"
board.indecies<-dat$Action=="Created" |  dat$Action=="Moved" | dat$Action=="Voted" | dat$Action =="ChangedColumn" | dat$ContextValue3=="BB1" | dat$ContextValue3=="BB2" | dat$ContextValue3=="BB3"| dat$ContextValue3=="BB4"

chat.dat<-dat[chat.indecies,]
board.dat<-dat[board.indecies,]
social.dat.1<-cbind.data.frame(board.dat$groupid,board.dat$studentid,board.dat$TimeStamp,board.dat$ContextValue3)
names(social.dat.1)<-c("groupid","studentid","TimeStamp","Interaction")


social.dat.1<-social.dat.1[order(social.dat.1$groupid,social.dat.1$TimeStamp),]

my.one.hot.func<-function(vector){
  v<-as.factor(vector)
  d<-matrix(0,nrow=length(v),ncol = nlevels(v))
  levels<-unique(v)
  colnames(d)<-levels
  for(i in 1:nrow(d))
    for(j in 1:ncol(d)){
      if(v[i]==levels[j]){d[i,j]<-1}
    }
  as.data.frame(d)
}

roll.avg <- function(x, n = 100){stats::filter(x, rep(1 / n, n), sides = 2)}
groups<-unique(social.dat.1$groupid)

board.dat<-as.list(1:length(groups))
board.cor<-as.list(1:length(groups))


for(i in 3:12){
  
  
  
  this.loop<-social.dat.1[social.dat.1$groupid==groups[i],]
  bb1.lines<-which(this.loop$Interaction=="BB1")
  bb2.lines<-which(this.loop$Interaction=="BB2")
  bb3.lines<-which(this.loop$Interaction=="BB3")
  bb4.lines<-which(this.loop$Interaction=="BB4")

  this.loop<-my.one.hot.func(this.loop$studentid)
  
  
  group.rolled<-as.data.frame(apply(this.loop,MARGIN = 2, roll.avg))
  corr.dat<-group.rolled
  group.rolled$index<-as.numeric(rownames(group.rolled))
  
  group.rolled<-gather(group.rolled,key="student",value="percent",-index)
  print(ggplot(group.rolled,aes(x=index,y=percent,color=student,group=student))+
          geom_line()+
          geom_vline(xintercept = bb1.lines,color="blue",alpha=0.1)+
          geom_vline(xintercept = bb2.lines,color="orange",alpha=0.1)+
          geom_vline(xintercept = bb3.lines,color="blue",alpha=0.1)+
          geom_vline(xintercept = bb4.lines,color="orange",alpha=0.1)+
          ggtitle(groups[i])  
  )
  
  
  corr.dat<-na.omit(corr.dat)
  cor.m<-as.matrix(cor(as.matrix(corr.dat)))
  assign(paste("cor.m",i,sep="."),
         cor.m)
  
  board.dat[[i]]<-group.rolled
  board.cor[[i]]<-cor.m
  print(i)
}

my.one.hot.func<-function(vector){
  v<-as.factor(vector)
  d<-matrix(0,nrow=length(v),ncol = nlevels(v))
  levels<-unique(v)
  colnames(d)<-levels
  for(i in 1:nrow(d))
    for(j in 1:ncol(d)){
      if(v[i]==levels[j]){d[i,j]<-1}
    }
  as.data.frame(d)
}
